<DOC><DOCNO> SJMN91-06010162 </DOCNO><ACCESS> 06010162 </ACCESS><DESCRIPT>  SMOKING; PRODUCT; COMPANY; PRESIDENT; BEGIN; MANAGEMENT; CHANGE  </DESCRIPT><LEADPARA>  Spencer J. Volk, who has led baking soda and fruit juice companies, will tryhis hand at tobacco as president and chief executive of the Liggett Group.;   Volk, 56, is joining Liggett, based in Durham, N.C., from the Church andamp; DwightCo., maker of Arm andamp; Hammer baking soda products. He will succeed James C.Turner, who is retiring at age 58, the company said.  </LEADPARA><SECTION>  Business  </SECTION><HEADLINE>  LIGGETT GROUP HIRES PRESIDENT  </HEADLINE><MEMO>  Shorter version ran on page 9F of the Afternoon final edition  </MEMO><TEXT>     Volk has been president and chief operating officer of Church andamp; Dwight,based in Princeton, N.J., since July 1989, when the company brought him in tobolster what was essentially a family-managed business.;    Volk once headedTropicana Products Inc., the fruit juice maker, where he was president in themid-1980s before the Beatrice Cos. sold it to Joseph E. Seagram andamp; Sons.;   Liggett, whose cigarette brands include Pyramid, Landamp;M and Chesterfield, waspurchased in 1986 by the investor Bennett S. LeBow from the British companyGrand Metropolitan PLC Liggett became a subsidiary of the Brooke Group, withLeBow as chairman, with plans to diversify into sports and entertainmentproducts.;    Brooke is also the parent of Impel Marketing and other LeBowventures, including Western Union and MAI Basic Four, a computer company.;   With 3 percent of the market, Liggett is the smallest of the domestic tobaccocompanies, and it gets much of its revenue  from discount cigarettes, whichprovide a lower profit compared with brand cigarettes.;    Management changesat Liggett began last summer with the retirement of its president, Kinsley DeyJr., who was succeeded by Turner. William Weksel, a business partner of LeBow,resigned in July as chairman of Liggett and later left MAI, where he waschairman and chief executive.;    Earlier in his career, Volk was a Procter andamp;Gamble brand manager in Canada and the joined Pepsico International, where hebecame senior vice president for Canada and Latin America.;    Volk is agraduate of Queens University and the Royal Military College, both in Ontario.  </TEXT><BYLINE>  New York Times  </BYLINE><COUNTRY>  USA  </COUNTRY><EDITION>  Home  </EDITION><CODE>  SJ  </CODE><NAME>  SAN JOSE MERCURY NEWS  </NAME><PUBDATE>   910110  </PUBDATE> <DAY>  Thursday  </DAY><MONTH>  January  </MONTH><PG.COL>  9F  </PG.COL><PUBYEAR>  1991  </PUBYEAR><REGION>  WEST  </REGION><STATE>  CA  </STATE><WORD.CT>  334  </WORD.CT><DATELINE>  Thursday, January 10, 199100010162,SJ1  </DATELINE><COPYRGHT>  Copyright 1991, San Jose Mercury News  </COPYRGHT><LIMLEN>  1  </LIMLEN><LANGUAGE>  ENG  </LANGUAGE></DOC>